* Overview
  {https://starship.rs/}[Starship] is a minimal, blazing-fast, and infinitely customizable prompt for any shell.
  We use it across all our shells (Fish, Bash, PowerShell) to provide a consistent prompt experience.

* Configuration Philosophy
  Our starship configuration focuses on:
  - *Nerd Font Icons*: Rich visual symbols for different programming languages and tools
  - *Comprehensive Language Support*: Icons for all major programming languages we use
  - *OS Detection*: Proper symbols for different operating systems
  - *Git Integration*: Clear branch and commit information
  - *Minimal Performance Impact*: Fast prompt rendering across all platforms

* Shell Integration
  Starship is initialized in all our shell configurations:
  - *Fish*: `starship init fish | source` in fish_config.norg:literate_config/shells/fish/fish_config.norg
  - *Bash*: `eval "$(starship init bash)"` in bashrc.norg:literate_config/shells/bash/bashrc.norg  
  - *PowerShell*: `Invoke-Expression (&starship init powershell)` in powershell_config.norg:literate_config/shells/powershell/powershell_config.norg

